    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Regents' School Ratings</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from New York State education commissioner, Richard P Mills, replies to May 6 news article on Board of Regents' efforts to raise achievement levels of schools</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''New York Regents Vote for Ratings of All Schools Based on Test Scores'' (news article, May 6): I disagree with the words ''punishing,'' ''shaming'' and ''branded'' used in your article to describe the Board of Regents accountability system. These are not the impulses that motivate the Regents' action. The focus is on improvement, and schools that improve the achievement of our children will be recognized.</p>
        <p>RICHARD P. MILLS  Commissioner of Education  Albany, May 8, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
